Protocols/Translator.html#/s:17MetaSeria.name: unwrap(meta:)
Protocols/Translator.html#/s:17MetaSeria.abstract: Extract the swift value from a meta, you initalized during decode(). If you don’t support the requested type directly, return nil. If you decoded to a Meta conforming to NilMetaProtocol, that Meta will not reach your method.

Protocols/Translator.html#/s:17MetaSeria.name: encode(_:)
Protocols/Translator.html#/s:17MetaSeria.abstract: Encodes the given meta representation of any encodable type to your (raw) representation type.

Protocols/Translator.html#/s:17MetaSeria.abstract: Decodes the given (raw) representation to a meta representation. Use a Meta extending NilMetaProtocol, to indicate that a value was nil.

Protocols/UnkeyedContainerMeta.html#/s:1.name: count
Protocols/UnkeyedContainerMeta.html#/s:1.abstract: the number of elements in the container, return 0, if no element is contained

Protocols/WrappingMeta.html#/s:17MetaSer.name: convert(wrapping:)

Protocols/Meta.html#/s:17MetaSerializati.abstract: returns the metas value. This may be nil, if the Meta has not been handled by a MetaEncoder or MetaDecoder, but if a Meta is passed to your Translator in encode() or decode() this value should not be nil, otherwise you dicovered a but in meta-serialization.

Protocols/DecodingRepresentation.html#/s.name: decode(type:)
